values:
Hey guys. Could you please actually tell me when something's going down?
I'm kinda sick of hearing about things an hour or whatever before it actually happens.
Or not hearing about it at all. Then I hear about what happened later and I get asked, "Hey, why didn't you come?"




If you could, that'd be great. Thanks.

1. Where were you when the ball dropped for 2006?
At jennas house, somewhere close to a tv. I think upstairs.

2. How did you get the idea for your screenname?
I like(d) Weezer a lot. And my uncle gave me wally as my only nickname ever. I think.

3. What song are you playing now, or wish you were playing?
Polaris - as usual

4. Has the death of a celebrity ever made you cry?
I cried when Elvis died.

5. What color underwear are you wearing?
The main color is blue. Light if it means anything.

6. Do you own an ipod?
I'm part of the white army.

7. What did you do this morning?
Slept in an hour. Then got ready and I still have a half hour.

8. What does your mom do for a living?
Stay at home, if I had it my way.

9. Where do you work?
No job.

10. What ended your last relationship?
Hmm. That's a good question.

11. What are the last 2 digits of your phone number?
71

12. What was the last concert you attended?
Changes.

13. Who was with you?
Cory and Molly.

14. What was the last movie you watched?
Phantom of the Opera. : )

15. Who do you dislike at the moment?
Does my throat count?

16. What food do you crave right now?
I'm not craving a whole lot at the moment.

17. Did you dream last night?
Couldn't tell you.


18. What was the last TV show you watched?
I don't know what it was, I was just flipping through the channels.

19. What is your favorite piece of jewelry?
I don't really wear jewelry.


20. What is to the left of you?
Almost our whole basement. Aside from that. A table with some junk on it. With a phone.

21. What was the last thing you ate?
Technically I had toothpaste in my mouth last. But I had cereal for breakfast.

22. Who is your best friend of the opposite ?
Kelseymeister.


23. Who last IMed you?
My sister.

24. Are you on any medication?
Zyrtec is fighting my allergies. Nothing else.

25. What side of the bed do you sleep on?
The top one.

26. What color shirt are you wearing?
Gray. "Let's  Wrap"


27. What color is your razor?
A whole slew. Gray, silver, black, blue.

28. What is your favorite frozen treat?
Ice cream haha.

29. How many piercings do you have?
None.

30. What's your favorite store?
The hobby shop is always fun. I don't know what regular store.

31. Are you thirsty right now?
No thanks.

32. Can you imagine yourself ever getting married?
Yes. 

33. Who's someone you haven't seen in a while and miss?
My sisters, my mom, Fil, Cory. 

34. What did you do last night?
Went to Jason's for Bible study and hangout.

35. Do you care what people think about you?
Sure, but not too much.

36. Have you ever done something to instigate trouble?
Yeah.

37. Do you like your nose?
I honestly don't care.

38. What color is your bedroom?
I think it's wallpapered.

39. When was the last time you worked out... seriously?
Swim season. 

40. What are your font colors on AIM?
Black and white.

41. Have you ever kissed a member of the same sex?
Yes. Not on the lips or anything. probably a relative. 

42. Where do you live?
Troy

43. Are you an aggressive driver?
I don't know. 

44. Who is your cell phone carrier?
Mr. Pocket.

45. Do you like the person who posted this last?
I'd say so.

46. What is across the room from you?
In front of me, there's a wall right behind the monitor. Hmm. Hard question cuz the computer is kinda in the middle of basement.

47. What is the thing you'd most want to change about yourself?
My ability to retain things I hear and learn. 

48. What color is your car?
Beige. Tan. Clear.

49. What do you smell like right now?
I can't say I've smelled myself yet this morning.

50. What is your favorite color?
Blue, green, orange.

Just feel like saying it:

10x100 @ 1.30
minute rest
10x100 @ 1.25
minute rest
10x100 @ 1.20
minute and a half rest
10x100 @ 1.20/1.15 alternate by 100
2 minute rest
5x100  @ 1.20/1.12 alternate by 100
2 minute rest
5x100  @ 1.20/1.10 alternate by 100

That was only the last set. We swam a total of 9000 yards today.

Ugh, happy new years.



Thanks for listening.

ps. I haven't seen like any of you college people all break. I've been busy during the day like everyday, so yeah. Thanks for trying.

Well, now I'm happy. I wasn't most of this week. But things are better now. : )


Yes!
I think it's funny that an error occurs in Internet Explorer only when I try to go to microsoft.com. Yeah.
That's basically all I wanted to say.
Merry Christmas! Actually now it's Boxing Day.
I'm taking a lifeguarding class during break.
I got a sweet scarf that's soft and comfy from Kelsey. : ) And a wallet cuz she's sick of the alien. : P
I wish I wasn't swimming during break. I have that and lifeguarding all day. Oh well.
That's all. Have a good rest of break. Stay safe! Safe travels!



Thanks for listening.

Hey y'all. ya'll. yal'l. 'yall. I haven't updated in a long time. I don't know or care how long. Someone update me on my friends page, cuz I haven't read those in a long time either. Just tell me the latest? Haha. Swimming's started, band's almost done. Practically. My body hurts. I feel like the summer, except then I could move and everything wasn't in pain. Yay. I'm contemplating doing a winterline next year. At Central that probably wouldn't work but Western it would work better. There's GLP in Grand Rapids. I'm going to miss drumming, not band. That's why I want to do a winterline. Hmm. So how are you all doing? I'm in a good mood. Maybe that's cuz it's the last day before break. What's kicking during break? I'm not guaranteeing that I can attend, but I'd love to know if there are things I'm invited to. I'd like to see the new Harry Potter movie. I might just wait to see it on video though. I'm not so interested in spending 7 bucks. Wow, I sound cheap. But really, I could easily just rent a movie and watch it over and over for much much much less than half that price. Polaris is so good. Thanks Alex. Hope you're at Thanksgiving. Eh, you don't do Livejournal.. Piggies! ; ) What else? Oh, I finished Season 3 of Alias. I like that show, I don't care what you people say. David Brent? from the Office was on it for an episode, Quentin Tarantino was in a few episodes, David Carradine was in it too. I'm not going to lie, I didn't really know their names. Thanks imdb. Ha. I should find a job, but it's kinda useless during swimming. Oh! I started a bible study thing with Jason, our youth pastor and another couple guys from youth group. It's fun stuff. Hmm. I think that's it for now. Hope you have a good day! Thanks for listening. ps. I was looking around on imdb and found that I was an assistant editor for a movie. That comes out next year? I'm in a movie!

So yeah, while I remember to do so, I need to ask you college students a question.
I'm thinking of what to buy for college computer-wise. Laptop, Desktop? What has benefitted you guys the most? I think some of you have both up at school with you and maybe which one you prefer more? I have another laptop here if I really need to take something to class with me. But yeah. Just tell me which you would recommend..


Thanks for listening.

P.S. Please actually tell me.

P.P.S. I should update sometime.


P.P.P.S. (is that possible?) Oh boy, my password is apparantly too easy to guess. So maybe I should change it. Who is really going to "hijack" my livejournal though. Lame.

So some guy called at like 5 and told me I was accepted to Western. His name is Chris too. I was at band, so I couldn't celebrate. Hmm. While on my awesome google homepage, I noticed this. It seems interesting enough. Take a look, g's.

It's fun, honest. So is Kelsey, she's the best. : )

Also, we got suede heads and Vega's. Oh man, fun stuff. Now we just have to get new drums..

Anyway, have a good evening/night.

 

 

Thanks for listening.

Hmm. I like Gmail. Cuz now I found out cool stuff.

Good luck HBO.

Don't worry about the URL, it's funny and unexpected.

I didn't know it was possible without big equipment.

Alright. Enough of my stupid stuff.

Hemeola's fun on quads.

I'm tired. Goodnight friends.

 

Thanks for listening. Have a good day.

I haven't listened to this song in forever. I haven't listened to Ben Folds in forever. Man. I usually also have hmm in my subject box. Cuz I don't bother. And that's the sound I think of when I'm thinking of what to write here.
So yeah. Percussion's good. I'm "the man" tonight.
Who replied to my last post about state? Hmm. I don't think so, sorry. Aside from the partying, rioting and humongous campus; that place isn't calling me much.
You know what's sweet? Drama. I love drama. Drama is like air for the band. Well for pretty much anybody. There is never enough drama apparantly.
Western next weekend! I hope it's still ok, Nick. :) I think it'll be fun.
I have a buncha bug bites. I think I know what they're from (aside from bugs) but I don't care.
3 days of band this week. We don't have a football game, do we?
This face is "trippy" in the infamous word of Brad.
I like drumming right now. Not like I didn't before, but it's fun. And you guys (drumline) make it more fun for me. Thanks. :)
Anyway, this was a pointless post. Then again, a lot of these are pointless.
Have a good day/evening. :)


Thanks for listening.

Well friends. It looks as though I have my college situation planned out.
I just (like 3 hours ago) got accepted to Western. :)
This entry is mainly for Nick and Pete and Kevin and Matt.
Sorry my Central buddies (and pretty much my whole family). I've betrayed you. I can be a spy for the enemy though. Both ways! If I had a death wish, I could wear a western shirt to central or a central shirt to western.
I probably sound really stupid now.
But I'm done with my computer science program and now I'm rocking out to JEW.
I'm kinda sad about the decision, but hopefully it'll all work out happy in the end.:)
Kelsey is awesome!
I'm kinda bored.
It's really warm in here and I'm wearing a dress shirt and khakis and stuff. Gosh.
Mary's looking up metalsmithing stuff for college.
I can't wait til this weekend. Homecoming with a bigger group than originally planned. :) Hanging out with Kelsey. Hanging out with the Power Trio(plus other cool guys/girls hopefully. :) 
Have a good day chillin's!



Thanks for listening.

Wanna see a sweet tenor (sixes?) player? Look no longer. Yeah, he's pretty sweet. I wish I could play like that.

That's about it. Oh, if you wanna see a goofy snare player, look no longer as well. Ha.

Hmm. I'm bored. Hope you all are having a good day.

See most of you tomorrow. Sadly, not all. :(

 

 

Thanks for listening.

A travesty has overcome this household:
I have no idea where my iPod is.
You should help me find it.
UPDATE: my dad found it under some clothes. And yes, it works. 

In other news, things are going well. We've learned Porkchop Sandwiches, which is fun.
I'm eating a freeze pop "huggy stick" that tastes like tropical fruit. It looks like the inside of a mango. Maybe it's mango. Isn't mango the name of a Jimmy Fallon thing or some other SNL guy?
This mouse is terrible. It's a serial mouse with a ball thing. The computer "couldn't find" the USB laser mouse.
I'm bored and I haven't updated in forever. I miss college people.
Ok. Off to find that cursed thing.
Have a good day! :)


Thanks for listening.

Sup? Yeah.
Those who feel like they should talk to me do. And I miss people and they don't talk to me anymore. And yeah. Then again, people don't talk much online. Or is it that I don't? I don't know.
I'm bored. I should go to bed. But I was watching Family Guy. So yeah.
I'm in a funky mood.
Certain people are getting on my nerves.
I don't understand what's going on. People change. Change sucks. That's what the past year + months taught me.
Let's make a mopey entry!.
The game was fun tonight. I met Matt's girlfriend. We talked to Keoleiandajd;lfadjn. "G-Maill Perry Yeah!" I don't really know how that goes but yeah. It's funny. The game just wasn't stressful. I felt like I was hanging out with friends. With instruments and weird clothing. Yeah.
*Start at good tempo*... *slow down* "drumline, stop rushing!"
"drumline, we need you in two minutes." "are we early?" "no actually you're late." good someone told us when to be there.
i like venting. maybe not on here but oh well. this is public knowledge. i think.
wow, i just totally gave up on capitalization. maybe it'll start up again later.
Sorry, this is a boring entry. I'll go now. I just felt like talking about random stuff. I think.
Have a good day everybody. 


Thanks for listening

So yeah. I totally spent the last half hour or so crying while reading the last few chapters of the new Harry Potter book.
Whether or not that should be public information, I don't know. Was it really that sad, I don't think so. It's sad that I cried, but the chapters weren't that sad I guess.
I haven't updated in forever. I apologize.
There's too much to say I think.
I'm done working. So I have a week. It feels like I totally missed out on summer.
I haven't seen a lot of friends. But who I saw, I had a blast with. I've seen a lot of youth group people, and that is by far not a problem. I love you guys.
I've spent a lot of time with Kelsey. :)
I'm glad work is over. It kinda tainted my mind. I didn't like that. Maybe I can clean it again. That's pretty much my only complaint about working.
Maybe I should be cool and keep a real journal. Or some place to write stuff that only I can read. Why am I typing all this? I don't know.
I didn't get to see a lot of people before they left for school, including my sisters. It feels like they came home yesterday. I'm not comfortable with that.
I should stop now.


Thanks for listening.

So it's kinda late, and I should go to bed. But I was bored and saw this. Yeah.
Kelsey's church tomorrow. :)
Yeah, have a goodnight and then day tomorrow.

And now you know.. the ressst of the story.

Kentucky was great. I had a lot of fun. I feel a lot closer to a lot of the people on that trip. Funny stuff happened (well a lot), weird stuff happened, umm. good stuff happened. There's not much to say?
Um.. Yeah.
I asked in my last entry who wanted to hang out. That applied to leavingfriends and stayingherefriends. Haha everybody replied to the Harry Potter stuff though. I'm in the third chapter. I'm usually a fast reader, honest. I just have to work everyday for pretty much the whole day.
So I guess nobody wants to hang out. I'd seriously love to.
So there is a "Fun House" in Royal Oak, but it certainly wasn't open when Kelsey and I tried to find it. Then we went into a creepy record store. Flipside scares me. Then we stayed in a park after hours. Then got a shake from Mickey D's. It's that new one. I don't like the Mango but the raspberry is good. Too bad it's a mix..
The music is weird this year. I dunno about that. No synth part?!
I'm bored.
Block party today. 4-8 at the church near Ellen's house. (Glen Oaks Alliance Church.) It'll be fun, Jason promises.
Also, party tomorrow at Kelsey's church. It's in the boonies though.
My wrists hurt. Same with most of my body. Poo on you, work.
This is a lame entry.
Have a good day! :)

Hey, this is kinda lame.
Has anybody gotten the new Harry Potter book? Where has the best price?
I feel like a nerd.
I need to drum, I already rubberbanded my sticks.
I need to make a real update. Well maybe not really.
I need to hang out with leaving friends soon. Like soon. Who's open and when? (This can also include friends that aren't leaving.)
Haha jubilant.
Ok.
Have a good day!
This is nifty I guess.. Not like you needed to know but oh well. Real names of people. So yeah. Now you actually know the rest of the story.
You know you're tired when you can't stop laughing when someone says poop.

I seemed to not have updated in a while.
Work has been hard but fun I guess. Kinda satisfying. I had Wednesday, Thursday and Friday off. :) Oh, Monday too.
I've done.. stuff since I last updated. Summer has been great. Friends and everything.
This weekend we went up north for the 4th. Kelsey came with us too. It was much fun. I don't know what to say about it though..
The temperature was so nice up there. Wow. My farmers tan was not evened out whatsoever, but my arms neck and face are darker. Goodness.
I've been watching a lot of Alias. I like it.
I felt like I haven't seen a lot of you in forever. So let's hang. Too bad I can't make plans cuz I don't know when I work or for how long. So call me when you're free or leave a message on my phone.
:)


And now you know the ressst of the story.

Setting:Some house in Fraser, someone's driveway.
Me:"Holy crap, what is that!?"
Uncle Jim:"That's a centipede."
Me:"It's huge!"
Uncle Jim:"It's industrial strength."
Me:"Pff, disgustrial strength."


And now you know the ressst of the story.

So it kinda was like Dad was driving me home from something, what it was I don't remember. Then when we get home, he tells me he found a horse or something. He tells me it's in the little playhouse shed thing in the back.
So I go back and I'm a little freaked out. I see it, woah it's a real horse! It's head sticks out the window and I pet it. I was like "Ah! I'm nice don't bite me!" And I think it spoke back to me, through it's mind or something. It was all white, I believe. My sisters come home and I yell at them to come around back and they see the horse and everything. They pet it.
So now I noticed that it's not really sitting on the ground. And by the way, it's body is shaped like a doghouse. With little legs. Woah.
So somehow we decide to build a bigger playhouse or something. So I guess the swim team ended up at my house. At least all I remember was working with Jon Kim. Maybe John. I don't know. I don't really remember what we were building cuz it made no sense.
Everything was all painted dark green and it was all shiny paint. And I think there were lace curtains or they were trimmed with lace. And I guess that this house was for the horse.
And somewhere in the middle of all this, there was a sequence of newspaper articles rushing at the camera. Like in movies where the papers just show up and you can read just the headlines. They were about a lost horse, then it was found, then we got to keep it.
Ok, I just remember building the house not much what the whole thing looked like.
Somewhere I was playing a board game at the end of the dream. It might have been Candyland.
</lj-cut>

It was crazy I tell you.
Phew. I'm still tired.
Did that make any sense to you? It didn't really to me.

Yetterday Kelsey and I, as I already told you, watched National Treasure.
We also went to Kurtis's soccer game, which got rained out. It was horrible, but we just laughed right through it. Then the dinner, then we watched more of the movie. :o) (Greg sent that face to me in an email once.)(Ellen makes those.)
Today we're going to my grandma's house. So I have to miss youth group. Poo.
